{
  "texts": [
    "Example 1: One-Off TrainingThis example represents an atomic version of algorithm training with a single training run followed by one evaluation run.",
    "We train once with 100,000 and once with 1,000,000 steps to compare the effect of increasing the training budget.",
    "To train using PPO we invoke the respective scripts from a terminal as follows: python train.py --algo ppo --distance euclidean and python train.py --algo ppo --distance euclidean --train_steps 1000000 The results of 100,000 training steps can be found in Fig. 7a.",
    "One can observe a steady improvement of MHC for about 80 evaluation steps.",
    "Afterwards, it is likely that the agent had not yet processed a sufficient amount of training observations, leading it to propose a series of actions that do not yield improvements and eventually run into a termination criterion."
  ]
}